headline: How Recent Developments Are Reshaping The Humana Investment Story
summary: The fair value estimate for Humana has nudged higher to about $288 from roughly $287 as analysts factor in slightly stronger long term revenue growth assumptions around 9.5%, supported by improving earnings visibility and steadier Medicare Advantage quality metrics. While the discount rate remains essentially unchanged near 6.96%, reflecting a stable perceived risk profile despite ongoing sector cyclicality, the small upward shift in fair value underscores a cautiously more optimistic view on...
